==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twaddells hydrometer
<hw>Twad"dell's
hy*drom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[After one
<etsep>Twaddell</etsep>, its inventor.]</ety> <def>A form of hydrometer
for liquids heavier than water, graduated with an arbitrary scale such
that the readings when multiplied by .005 and added to unity give the
specific gravity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twaddle</ent>⟦br⟧
